```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.boxplot(column='Body_Mass__g_', by='Species')
    ax.set_title('')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass across different penguin species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45 if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20 else 0)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['Beak_Length__mm_'], data['Beak_Depth__mm_'])
    plt.xlabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between beak length and beak depth?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_flipper_length = data.groupby('Sex')['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean()
    avg_flipper_length.plot(kind='bar', rot=0)
    
    plt.title("What is the average flipper length for male and female penguins?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Sex")
    plt.ylabel("Average Flipper Length (mm)")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    islands = data['Island'].unique()
    for island in islands:
        island_data = data[data['Island'] == island]['Beak_Length__mm_']
        plt.hist(island_data, alpha=0.5, label=island)
    
    plt.xlabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Island')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of beak length across different islands?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
